<TITLE> Cabinet okays plan to change BERC law </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 7 (bdnews24.com)  The interim cabinet has approved a proposal to amend the Bangladesh Energy Regulatory Commission Law-2003. A government handout on Sunday said the a cabinet meeting chaired by chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed approved the proposal. The chief adviser's press secretary, Syed Fahim Munaim, later said the meeting also provisionally approved the amendment of 'the Town Improvement Act-1953' to pace up the management of the city development Rajdhani Unnayan Kartipakkha. The meeting asked authorities to place together two separate proposals of defence and home ministries on hiking financial allowance for the members of armed forces who were awarded for bravery. The meeting provisionally approved 'the Non-government Educational Institutions Governing Committee Ordinance-2008' and 'the Dhaka Children Hospital Ordinance-2008'. A proposal on signing a memorandum of understanding between Bangladesh and Thailand to exchange agricultural technology and research was also approved. The committee also approved 'the Financial Reporting Ordinance-2008'. Members of the advisory council and special assistants to the CA, cabinet secretary, and secretaries to the relevant ministries attended the meeting. bdn
